VCU Basketball Coach Shaka Smart Gets 8-Year Deal After Run to Final Four

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-04-04T23:18:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/vcu-basketball-coach-shaka-smart-gets-8-year-deal-after-run-to-final-four.html
Virginia Commonwealth University
basketball coach Shaka Smart has agreed to a new eight-year
contract after leading the Rams to the Final Four of the
national men’s basketball tournament.  “Coach Smart’s contributions to the university are
unquantifiable,” VCU President Michael Rao said in a statement
on the school’s website. Financial terms will be disclosed when
the contract is completed, the school said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  